{"title":"The Hudski Dualist is a Do it all ATB With Personality","link":"https://bikerumor.com/hudski-dualist-atb-sea-otter/","date":1744484253000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-hero.webp\" width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" alt=\"(Photos / R. Frazelle)\" /></p>\n<p>San Rafael, California, is the home of <a href=\"https://hudskibikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Hudski Bikes</a>. And here at Sea Otter 2025, they launched a new bike, called the <a href=\"https://hudskibikes.com/products/dualist-all-terrain-bike?variant=41527490215999\" target=\"_blank\">Dualist</a>. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/hudski-dualist-do-it-all-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">We teased it</a> last year, and now the new “Jack of all trades, and a master of most” is here. It can be all the bikes in one: a versatile rigid MTB, a bikepacker, a gravel bike, or a city bike. It looks like it can do it all.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-front-side.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-front-side.webp\" alt=\"Sea Otter Hudski Dualist front side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-front-side.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-front-side-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-front-side-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-front-side-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos / R. Frazelle)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Dualist rocks flip chip axles for both front and rear wheels. It has Boost rear spacing and is UDH compatible. It can be set up however you want, with most of the parts in your parts bin. Or, you can buy the complete bike, which is decked out with a Shimano SLX group. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-back-side.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-back-side.webp\" alt=\"Sea Otter Hudski Dualist back side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-back-side.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-back-side-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-back-side-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-back-side-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Dualist pulls inspiration from the DNA of the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/city-bike-gravel-bike-mtb-the-hudski-doggler-combines-modern-standards-unique-style/\" target=\"_blank\">Hudski Doggler</a>, keeping the Doggler’s best attributes, the Dualist takes it to the next level with bigger tire clearance and UDH compatibility.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-dt-logo.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-dt-logo.webp\" alt=\"Sea Otter Hudski Dualist dt logo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-dt-logo.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-dt-logo-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-dt-logo-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-dt-logo-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-cool-head-badge.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-cool-head-badge.webp\" alt=\"Sea Otter Hudski Dualist cool head badge\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-cool-head-badge.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-cool-head-badge-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-cool-head-badge-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-cool-head-badge-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The frame is made from 6061 aluminum, and the fork is full carbon. The geo has been slightly tweaked when compared to its inspiration, the Doggler. The geo lends itself to be stable when going down rough descents, but still “snappy and playful on more subdued rides”.   </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Flippin’ the Chip</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-flip-chip-front.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-flip-chip-front.webp\" alt=\"Sea Otter Hudski Dualist flip chip front\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-flip-chip-front.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-flip-chip-front-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-flip-chip-front-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-flip-chip-front-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rack-mounts.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rack-mounts.webp\" alt=\"Sea Otter Hudski Dualist rack mounts\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rack-mounts.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rack-mounts-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rack-mounts-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rack-mounts-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Dualist’s versatility comes from the front and rear flip chip. The front axle can be adjusted +/- 10mm, and the rear by +/- 15mm. That means you can play around with 4 distinct geometry settings, which is pretty cool.  </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-flip-chip-rear-do.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-flip-chip-rear-do.webp\" alt=\"Sea Otter Hudski Dualist flip chip rear do\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-flip-chip-rear-do.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-flip-chip-rear-do-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-flip-chip-rear-do-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-flip-chip-rear-do-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-drop-out.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-drop-out.webp\" alt=\"Sea Otter Hudski Dualist drop out\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-drop-out.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-drop-out-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-drop-out-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-drop-out-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rear-brake-dropo-out.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rear-brake-dropo-out.webp\" alt=\"Sea Otter Hudski Dualist rear brake dropo out\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rear-brake-dropo-out.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rear-brake-dropo-out-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rear-brake-dropo-out-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rear-brake-dropo-out-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-DO-back-side.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-DO-back-side.webp\" alt=\"Sea Otter Hudski Dualist DO back side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-DO-back-side.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-DO-back-side-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-DO-back-side-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-DO-back-side-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>435/44</strong> – offers the shortest wheelbase and the longest trail. This setting will increase steering stability. Hudski recommends using a 700c, 29″ wheel, with a 2.4″ or 50c tire. Great setting for enjoying single track. </li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>450/54</strong> – This is the longest wheelbase and shortest trail. This setting will give you the best and most even front and rear weight distribution. Great setting for bikepacking and commuting, while still offering nimble and fun steering.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>435/54</strong> – This is the best setting for riding the Dualist like a rigid mountain bike. The shorter chainstays offer a sharp, precise, and playful rear end, while keeping the steering nimble.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>450/44</strong> – The setting will get you a little closer to the geo of the Doggler. This means you’ll get identical front and rear offsets, putting the rider in a position where weight distribution is more over the front axle. You can run 27.5 x 2.8 (and some 3.0) tires with this setting.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Dualist Geometry</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-geo-chart-e1744483524413.webp\"><img width=\"802\" height=\"646\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-geo-chart-e1744483524413.webp\" alt=\"Sea Otter Hudski Dualist geo chart\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-geo-chart-e1744483524413.webp 802w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-geo-chart-e1744483524413-297x239.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-geo-chart-e1744483524413-120x97.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-geo-chart-e1744483524413-768x619.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Dualist Retail and Frame Features</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rear-chainstay-yoke.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rear-chainstay-yoke.webp\" alt=\"Sea Otter Hudski Dualist rear chainstay yoke\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rear-chainstay-yoke.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rear-chainstay-yoke-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rear-chainstay-yoke-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rear-chainstay-yoke-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-brake-mounts-fork.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-brake-mounts-fork.webp\" alt=\"Sea Otter Hudski Dualist brake mounts fork\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-brake-mounts-fork.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-brake-mounts-fork-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-brake-mounts-fork-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-brake-mounts-fork-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rack-mounts-chain-stay.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rack-mounts-chain-stay.webp\" alt=\"Sea Otter Hudski Dualist rack mounts chain stay\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rack-mounts-chain-stay.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rack-mounts-chain-stay-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rack-mounts-chain-stay-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Sea-Otter-Hudski-Dualist-rack-mounts-chain-stay-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $2400 (complete)</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Frame: 6061 Alkuminum Alloy</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fork: Carbon fiber</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Testing: Mountain ISO 4210-6-2017</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Cable Routing: Internal through frame ports</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Max Tire Size: SWB-29 x 2.5″//LWB-27.5 x 2.8″//SWB-27.5 x 3.0″ </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Max Chainring: 38t @ 52mm chainline</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Bottom Bracket: Threaded BSA 73mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Headset: 44ZS upper 1-1/8″/44EC lower 1-1/2″</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Seatpost: 31.6mm, Clamp: 34.9mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Brake Mount: Post Mount</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Axle Spacing: Boost (15×110, 12×148)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Hanger: UDH</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Click the link below to get more details.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://hudskibikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">HudskiBikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/hudski-dualist-atb-sea-otter/\">The Hudski Dualist is a Do it all ATB With Personality</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"6d6e4ff3a9308e3ad804681aa1bb8eeb2d47c9a73651730475cced367e2311e4","category":"Cycling"}